comments.body: I have enabled versioning on all pdc describe buckets following the updated documentation in the rdss-handbook

@acozine I downgraded the bundler version to 2.3.24 and was able to deploy ruby 3.1. I noticed the ruby_test.yml file you added only for bibdata-alma-worker-staging1. I can see `usr/lib/ruby/vendor_ruby/phusion_passenger` passenger in this machine. I cannot see `usr/lib/ruby/vendor_ruby/phusion_passenger` on the server machine bibdata-alma-staging1 and this is why I get a forbidden status only from this machine; I found this in the nginx logs `pulsys@bibdata-alma-staging1:~$ sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/error.log`: 'directory index of "/opt/bibdata/current/public/" is forbidden,'. 
In the bibdata-alma-worker-stgaing1 machine I checked if passenger is loading by running `/usr/bin/passenger-config --root`. Then  I tunneled in bibdata-alma-worker-staging1 where you have the ruby_test to run. Passenger is there but fails to load because of a gem version that I need to figure out how to change it. I will try again to install a different bundler version that supports the specific default gem that throws the error or I will start the ruby 3.1 upgrade from scratch. See you next week!
